          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An 8-O-18 beam with energy of 117 MeV was used. The",
                "8-O-18 beam was kept to about 5 enA, which is",
                "measured by a Faraday cup."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A silicon dE/E telescope was used to identify",
                "the light ejectile particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two LaBr3(Ce)detectors with a size of 4 inch",
                "in diameter x 5 inch in length were used for",
                "gamma-ray detection."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "8-O-16",
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " (1) The dE detectors with trapezoidal shape are",
                "arranged to form a ring shape around the beam axis in",
                "an angular range of 22-39 degree relative to the beam",
                "direction. The thickness is 75 um. (2) The E detector",
                "is an annular-type detector and has 16 ring-shaped",
                "strips. The resolution of the scattering angle of the",
                "ejectile is around 1.2 degree. The thickness is 300 um."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The correction of the integrated 8-O-18 beam current,",
                "the target thickness, the absolute detection",
                "efficiency of the LaBr3 detectors, and the absolute",
                "branching ratio of gamma lines were done."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SURGT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Surrogate technique: The 92Zr(18O,16O)94Zr",
                "and 90Zr(18O,16O)92Zr reactions represent",
                "93Zr(n,g)94Zr and 91Zr(n,g)92Zr, respectively. The",
                "gamma intensities 94.9% (919 keV) and 97.2% (934 keV)",
                "were adopted for identification of 94Zr and 92Zr,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
